Robot.html.title: Robot
Robot.html.name: Robot
Robot.html.description: Main Robot class Handles electron task window initialization and program execution start

Robot.html#.EXEC_FOLDER.title: <static, readonly> EXEC_FOLDER
Robot.html#.EXEC_FOLDER.name: EXEC_FOLDER
Robot.html#.EXEC_FOLDER.description: Where to find the fetched task's program on disk

Robot.html#id.title: id
Robot.html#id.name: id
Robot.html#id.description: Fetches credentials from configuration using api_helper.credentials()

Robot.html#_end.title: _end()
Robot.html#_end.name: _end
Robot.html#_end.description: Ends robot's execution Clean stop and delete of robot and any running task Destroys and delete the task's window

Robot.html#run.title: <async> run()
Robot.html#run.name: run
Robot.html#run.description: Main entry point of robot execution First fetch potential pending Task, then starts it and await its completion Always ends with a recursive call to itself after 5s

Robot.html#stop.title: stop()
Robot.html#stop.name: stop
Robot.html#stop.description: Public function to stop robot execution, triggered by closing the task's window Internaly calls Robot._end() with WindowClosedDuringProcess error

ScriptStep.html.title: ScriptStep
ScriptStep.html.name: ScriptStep
ScriptStep.html.description: Step that executes a script on the web client

ScriptStep.html#consoleMessage.title: consoleMessage()
ScriptStep.html#consoleMessage.name: consoleMessage
ScriptStep.html#consoleMessage.description: Callback for window's 'console-message' event Store the console message to fetch error from it

ScriptStep.html#_executeScript.title: <async> _executeScript()
ScriptStep.html#_executeScript.name: _executeScript
ScriptStep.html#_executeScript.description: Bind 'console-message' event callback and execute step's script Any data returned by the script will be appended to sessionData object

ScriptStep.html#init.title: <async> init()
ScriptStep.html#init.name: init
ScriptStep.html#init.description: Initialize the step Prepend step's env and task's sessionData to the executed script so the variables can be accessed inside the web client

ScriptStep.html#_timedOut.title: _timedOut()
ScriptStep.html#_timedOut.name: _timedOut
ScriptStep.html#_timedOut.description: Triggers a StepError when step's timeout is reached

ScriptStep.html#_stepActionsIterator.title: <generator> _stepActionsIterator()
ScriptStep.html#_stepActionsIterator.name: _stepActionsIterator
ScriptStep.html#_stepActionsIterator.description: Handle step actions Yields for an inputUrl to match with startWith and endWith if provided Triggers script execution and downloads

ScriptStep.html#execute.title: execute()
ScriptStep.html#execute.name: execute
ScriptStep.html#execute.description: Entry point for step execution Create a stepActionIterator generator and triggers startWith url if provided

ScriptStep.html#inputUrl.title: inputUrl()
ScriptStep.html#inputUrl.name: inputUrl
ScriptStep.html#inputUrl.description: Provides rendered url to stepActionIterator If endWith url is reached, resolve step's promise

ScriptStep.html#domReady.title: domReady()
ScriptStep.html#domReady.name: domReady
ScriptStep.html#domReady.description: Change DOM state boolean and triggers any pending script

Task.html.title: Task
Task.html.name: Task
Task.html.description: Handle Task Fetch task, parse task program and config, steps execution, task log file

Task.html#.PENDING.title: <static, readonly> PENDING
Task.html#.PENDING.name: PENDING
Task.html#.PENDING.description: Get Task PENDING status id from api_helper.credentials()

Task.html#.PROCESSING.title: <static, readonly> PROCESSING
Task.html#.PROCESSING.name: PROCESSING
Task.html#.PROCESSING.description: Get Task PROCESSING status id from api_helper.credentials()

Task.html#.FAILED.title: <static, readonly> FAILED
Task.html#.FAILED.name: FAILED
Task.html#.FAILED.description: Get Task FAILED status id from api_helper.credentials()

Task.html#.DONE.title: <static, readonly> DONE
Task.html#.DONE.name: DONE
Task.html#.DONE.description: Get Task DONE status id from api_helper.credentials()

Task.html#snippetUtils.title: <readonly> snippetUtils
Task.html#snippetUtils.name: snippetUtils
Task.html#snippetUtils.description: Returns a snippetUtils provided to Step constructor

Task.html#.fetch.title: <async, static> fetch() → {Task}
Task.html#.fetch.name: fetch
Task.html#.fetch.description: Fetch any pending task from the API matching Robot id Upon succesful fetch, create new Task class and set task's status to PROCESSING in API

Task.html#elapsedTime.title: elapsedTime() → {number}
Task.html#elapsedTime.name: elapsedTime
Task.html#elapsedTime.description: Gives the time since task's start in milliseconds

Task.html#log.title: log( param )
Task.html#log.name: log
Task.html#log.description: Writes log to task's log file, sent to the API after execution Clean json and error log handled Writes to Task._logFilePath

Task.html#sendLogFile.title: <async> sendLogFile()
Task.html#sendLogFile.name: sendLogFile
Task.html#sendLogFile.description: Sends log file to the API

Task.html#init.title: <async> init()
Task.html#init.name: init
Task.html#init.description: Initialize Task Downloads task's program and unzip it Parses its config file

Task.html#executeSteps.title: <async> executeSteps()
Task.html#executeSteps.name: executeSteps
Task.html#executeSteps.description: Loop over steps array Initialize a ScriptStep or SequenceStep depending on step's type Initialize and start the Step then awaits it completion

Task.html#executeErrorSteps.title: <async> executeErrorSteps()
Task.html#executeErrorSteps.name: executeErrorSteps
Task.html#executeErrorSteps.description: Normalize onError array and trigger error steps execution Error step can be a step index, a step name, a step definition, or an array of those types Once onError definition resolve to a valid array of steps, Task.executeSteps is called

Task.html#failed.title: <async> failed()
Task.html#failed.name: failed
Task.html#failed.description: Called upon execution failure Logs error to file, update task and execution to Task.FAILED through API

Task.html#finalize.title: <async> finalize()
Task.html#finalize.name: finalize
Task.html#finalize.description: Called upon execution success Logs session data to file, update task and execution to Task.DONE

Task.html#start.title: <async> start()
Task.html#start.name: start
Task.html#start.description: Initialize and start Task Always sends task's log file to the API before returning

Task.html#stop.title: stop()
Task.html#stop.name: stop
Task.html#stop.description: Stops pending downloads and reject Task's promise

Task.html#inputUrl.title: inputUrl()
Task.html#inputUrl.name: inputUrl
Task.html#inputUrl.description: Called for each url the client loaded Input url is sent to the ongoing step and is used to match startWith/endWith step configuration

Task.html#willDownload.title: willDownload()
Task.html#willDownload.name: willDownload
Task.html#willDownload.description: Triggered by a download event from the client It will set the file save path and name, and build an entry for the download array with informations about the download

Task.html#domReady.title: domReady()
Task.html#domReady.name: domReady
Task.html#domReady.description: When DOM state change, propagate its state to steps to stop/start script executions
